  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with Nonvalvular Atrial Fibrillation (NVAF) aged 80 years or older who are
             ineligible for available oral anticoagulation therapy

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with active bleeding

          -  Patients who have poorly controlled hypertension

          -  Patients who have liver dysfunction accompanied with disorder of blood coagulation
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
